# Home Assistant Environment Variables
# ⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL - See compose.yml for important warnings
#
# This is a reference example. Home Assistant OS is the recommended installation method.
# See: https://www.home-assistant.io/installation/

# ============================================================================
# Timezone Configuration
# ============================================================================
TZ=Asia/Seoul
# Timezone for Home Assistant
# Default: Asia/Seoul
# See: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones

# ============================================================================
# Port Configuration (for bridge network mode)
# ============================================================================
# HASS_PORT=8123
# Home Assistant web interface port
# Default: 8123
# Only used when network_mode is set to bridge instead of host

# ============================================================================
# PostgreSQL Configuration (Optional)
# ============================================================================
# Uncomment if using PostgreSQL instead of default SQLite
# POSTGRES_DB=homeassistant
# POSTGRES_USER=homeassistant
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=homeassistant
# WARNING: Change password in production!

# ============================================================================
# USAGE NOTES
# ============================================================================
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT LIMITATIONS:
# - Add-ons NOT supported (critical Home Assistant feature)
# - USB device passthrough required for Zigbee/Z-Wave
# - Complex network setup needed for mDNS device discovery
# - High resource usage (2-8GB RAM)
#
# RECOMMENDED: Use Home Assistant OS instead
# https://www.home-assistant.io/installation/
#
# Setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Configure timezone if needed
#
# 3. Start service:
#    docker compose up -d
#
# 4. Access Home Assistant:
#    http://localhost:8123 (or server IP if using host network)
#
# 5. Complete onboarding:
#    - Create admin account
#    - Configure location
#    - Set up integrations
#
# Network Mode Options:
# - host: Recommended for device discovery (mDNS, SSDP)
# - bridge: Requires port mapping, limited device discovery
#
# USB Device Configuration:
# Edit compose.yml to add devices:
#   devices:
#     - /dev/ttyUSB0:/dev/ttyUSB0  # Zigbee dongle
#     - /dev/ttyACM0:/dev/ttyACM0  # Z-Wave dongle
#
# PRODUCTION NOTES:
# ============================================================================
# This configuration is for testing/development only.
# For production:
# 1. Use Home Assistant OS (official recommendation)
# 2. If Docker is required, review all security implications
# 3. Configure proper backups
# 4. Set up SSL/TLS via reverse proxy
# 5. Review network security
# ============================================================================
